9. Donatus observes that quoniam is here used in the mere sense of a temporal conjunction, which the word is logically entitled to, being but a compound of quom and iam. Plautus has it so not unfrequently, e.g. Tria. 112 quoniam hinc iturust ipsus in Seleuciam. ibid. 149 quo- uiam hinc profectu-sc ire pereqre Charmides. We may observo the same change of the two notions of temporality and causality in the Ger- man conj. weil, which has now almost entirely lost its temporal sense, though this was the original one.
